---
// WhatIs — grounding section between Hero and ProofStrip.
// No cards, no grid. A single centered text block that answers
// "wait, what exactly is Formspec?" before the reader scrolls further.
---

<section class="whatis-section" aria-labelledby="whatis-heading">
  <div class="whatis-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow" aria-hidden="true">What is Formspec</div>
    <h2 class="whatis-title" id="whatis-heading">
      AI helps you build them, fill them out,<br />
      and put the data to work.
    </h2>
    <p class="whatis-body">
      Formspec is the first form framework where AI is built into every stage of the lifecycle:
      creating forms, modifying them, maintaining them over time, helping people fill them out,
      and transforming the outcome data into whatever your systems need. No coding at any step.
    </p>
    <p class="whatis-body">
      Every form is a single readable file — not a database, not a vendor platform. Open it
      in any text editor, email it to a colleague, check it into version control. Business rules
      and validation live in one layer; visual design lives in another. Change the look without
      touching the rules. Pass an audit on the logic, then let your UX team iterate on the
      interface without re-certification.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .whatis-section {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: 4.5rem 0;
  }

  .whatis-inner {
    max-width: 44rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 2.5rem);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .section-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .whatis-title {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }

  .whatis-body {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
